    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="structDali_1_1TypeTraits" kindref="compound">TypeTraits</ref> specialization for <ref refid="classDali_1_1Pair" kindref="compound">Dali::Pair</ref>. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Delegates to <ref refid="structDali_1_1Detail_1_1PairIsTrivial" kindref="compound">Detail::PairIsTrivial</ref> rather than inheriting from <ref refid="structDali_1_1BasicTypes" kindref="compound">BasicTypes</ref>&lt;<ref refid="classDali_1_1Pair" kindref="compound">Pair</ref>&lt;T1,T2&gt;&gt; or reading <ref refid="structDali_1_1TypeTraits" kindref="compound">TypeTraits</ref>&lt;T1&gt;/TypeTraits&lt;T2&gt;, so that this specialization can be instantiated with incomplete T1 or T2 (e.g. when <ref refid="classDali_1_1Pair" kindref="compound">Pair</ref>&lt;T1,T2&gt; appears in a type alias).</para>
<para>The compiler intrinsics that require complete types live inside <ref refid="structDali_1_1Detail_1_1PairIsTrivial" kindref="compound">Detail::PairIsTrivial</ref>, which is only instantiated when code actually reads IS_TRIVIAL_TYPE - at that point both types must already be complete, so the intrinsics are safe to evaluate.</para>
<para>@SINCE_2_5.16 </para>
